Job Title: MERN & Smart Contract Developer

Location: Remote
Type: Full-time
Budget: $1500~$2000 a week
Company: Streym LTD
Location: England
Websites: https://streym.com

About Us:  
We are an innovative company focused on revolutionizing the eCommerce industry through blockchain technology. We are currently developing a blockchain-based warranty system that leverages NFTs to provide seamless warranty management for retailers and customers.

Job Description:  
We are looking for a skilled MERN & Smart Contract Developer to join our team. You will be responsible for enhancing our existing application and implementing smart contracts based on specific business logic. 

Here is our project:
https://bitbucket.org/streym-ltd/nft-warranty-system/src/main/

Responsibilities:

1. UI Enhancement:
   - Update the current user interface according to the new design outlined in our Figma prototype: [Figma Design](https://www.figma.com/design/0UNPsOjgiQorLRFXkZktVv/E-commerce-Grid).

2. Develop smart contracts implementing the following logic:
   1) Retailer Functions:
     - Allow retailers to purchase NFT warranty cards using Metamask upon receiving an order request.
     - Ensure gas fees are charged to the retailer, not the customer.
     - Enable retailers to set warranty information at the time of NFT purchase.
     - Utilize the `safeTransferFrom()` function of ERC721 tokens to send warranty cards to customers.
     - Generate and send a unique token ID to customers via email after purchase.

   2) Customer Functions:
     - Allow customers to verify ownership by entering their unique token ID received via email, using the `ownerOf` function for ERC721 soulbound tokens.
     - Display warranty period and other relevant information on the verification page.
     - Implement a decay mechanism for NFTs, ensuring they stop functioning after the warranty period or after redemption.

Requirements:
- Proficiency in MERN stack (MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, Node.js).
- Strong experience with smart contract development on Ethereum (Solidity).
- Familiarity with ERC721 standards and NFT functionality.
- Experience with Metamask and integrating blockchain solutions into web applications.
- Understanding of email services for sending token IDs.
- Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.

What We Offer:
- Competitive salary and benefits.
- Flexible working hours and remote work options.
- Opportunities for professional growth and development.
- A collaborative and innovative work environment.

How to Apply:  
If you are excited about the intersection of blockchain technology and eCommerce and want to be part of our mission, please send your resume and a brief cover letter via DM.


